- Sure.
- Okay. You take care.

232
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:28,796
How 'bout tonight?

233
00:17:29,673 --> 00:17:33,509
No, I don't think so, Sally. Not tonight. But I'll tell you what I'll do: I'll check with the doctor, see when you get out.

234
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:36,512
- No. They want to keep me for observation.
- Wait a minute.

235
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:40,892
- Sally, you really gotta stay in bed.
- I don't like to be observed.

236
00:17:40,976 --> 00:17:44,062
Well, I'm sorry, but there's really
nothing I can do about that.

237
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:46,439
Please. I really don't like hospitals.

238
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:48,816
- Wai -- All right.
- I have to get out of here. It's making me n --

239
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,319
I'll make you a deal. Okay?
This is the deal.

240
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:54,405
You stay here, I'll get your clothes, and then
when I come back we'll go out and have a drink.

241
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,949
Okay? All right?

242
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:59,410
Well... I need shoes and a coat.

243
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:03,498
Yes, I'll get them.
But if you don't stay, I'm not coming back.

244
00:18:03,582 --> 00:18:05,249
- Okay.
- All right.

245
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:12,590
- [ Chattering ]
- [ Phones Ringing ]

246
00:18:26,021 --> 00:18:29,398
[ Man ] Looked like it was gonna be all right,
but this guy Jack Terry --

247
00:18:29,483 --> 00:18:32,276
He took her out of the car.
That's him over there.

248
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:35,488
He's being a real horse's ass and I don't know
how we're gonna keep the lid on this guy.

249
00:18:36,532 --> 00:18:40,159
Get some men out there. I want this place sealed.
I'm not gonna have this turn into some kind of a circus.

250
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:42,328
Sir, this is the guy here.
He was right there when it happened.

251
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:44,789
- Now he saw the whole thing.
- He's the one who saw it?

252
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:48,209
Yes. His name is Jack Terry.
He says he pulled the girl out of the car.

253
00:18:54,049 --> 00:18:57,135
I want to talk to you.
And to the girl too. Where is she?

254
00:18:57,219 --> 00:18:59,303
- She's in there.
- All right, she's asleep.

255
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:02,640
If you wanna talk to me, make it quick,
'cause I've had enough tonight. I wanna go home.

256
00:19:02,724 --> 00:19:04,851
Is there a room some place around here
we can talk in private?

257
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:07,854
Yes, sir, I'll take care of it.
Thornwall, would you secure that room for us?

258
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,690
- Captain, I want these men checked out.
- Officer.

259
00:19:11,441 --> 00:19:14,068
- What's going on here?
- Car accident. Guy got killed.

260
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:18,072
- I know that. But what's the big deal?
- Did you know the guy was McRyan?

261
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:19,657
That's Governor McRyan?

262
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:22,952
That stiff on the stretcher
was probably our next president.

263
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:27,123
- Hell, he had my vote.
- [ Quietly ] Jesus Christ.

264
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:32,253
Let's talk in here.

265
00:19:42,764 --> 00:19:45,892
- You pulled the girl out of that car?
- Yes.

266
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:51,606
Well, I would like for you to forget about her,
forget you ever saw her.

267
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:54,275
Wait a minute.

268
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:55,943
Wh-Who are you?

269
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:59,197
My name is Lawrence Henry.
I work for Governor McRyan.

270
00:19:59,281 --> 00:20:00,573
Oh.

271
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:02,825
He was also a friend.

272
00:20:03,994 --> 00:20:05,912
He was my friend.

273
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:10,208
Well, look, I-I'm -- I'm very sorry
about the governor...

274
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:15,963
and I-I -- I obviously would have
loved to have saved his life too, but, uh --

275
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:18,049
I mean, I was there and she was there.

276
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:21,344
Yeah, well, we know what happened,
but the governor is dead now...

277
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:25,473
and... we don't want to
embarrass his family.

278
00:20:26,475 --> 00:20:29,644
Do you have any idea what the press would do
if they got ahold of a thing like this?

279
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:32,730
What do you want me to do,
just say she wasn't here?

280
00:20:32,814 --> 00:20:35,942
- I already told the police.
- That's already taken care of.

281
00:20:38,528 --> 00:20:40,196
All right, what about the girl?

282
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:43,824
I'll talk to her.
I'm sure she'll cooperate.

283
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:47,954
So one playmate just vanishes
from McRyan's car just like that? Pfft!

284
00:20:48,038 --> 00:20:51,082
- That's right.
- Oh, Jesus. I don't know. I don't --

285
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:53,876
C-C-Can't you keep your mouth shut?

286
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:56,462
It's better the governor died alone.

287
00:20:57,839 --> 00:21:01,509
I just don't know if I can do that.
I mean, I was there, she was there and --

288
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:03,678
Who gives a damn that you were there?

289
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:08,766
You want to tell his wife that he died
with his hand up some girl's dress?

290
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:10,768
Or maybe you'd rather
she read it in the papers!

291
00:21:10,852 --> 00:21:14,105
Well, that is what happened.
I mean, that is the truth, isn't it?

292
00:21:14,189 --> 00:21:16,899
Well, what difference
does that make to you...

293
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:23,030
when it would make a great deal of difference
to his family?

294
00:21:27,035 --> 00:21:29,036
[ Exhales ]

295
00:21:30,831 --> 00:21:32,748
- All right.
- Good.

296
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:35,251
I'll slip you and the girl out the back.

297
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,884
How about your place?

298
00:21:43,969 --> 00:21:46,178
You don't want to go home, do you?

299
00:21:47,514 --> 00:21:51,142
[ Yawns ] They told you
who was in the car, right?

300
00:21:51,226 --> 00:21:52,476
Yeah.

301
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:57,648
Well, some smart reporter could figure
I was there too, you know.

302
00:21:57,733 --> 00:22:01,736
They've got my purse
with my name, my address.

303
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:04,405
They're gonna be camped
on my doorstep.

304
00:22:04,489 --> 00:22:08,743
What about my doorstep? I'm the one
who pulled you out of that wreck, didn't l?

305
00:22:08,827 --> 00:22:11,120
[ Yawning ]
Yeah, right.

306
00:22:11,204 --> 00:22:13,247
Let's go to a motel.

307
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:14,749
[ Chuckles ]

308
00:22:16,793 --> 00:22:20,338
First it's a drink. Then it's my place.
Now it's a motel.

309
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:23,215
Boy, things are really moving fast tonight,
aren't they, Sally?

310
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:35,811
Whoops.

311
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:38,731
Stop over here for a second.

312
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:41,984
Fourteen. All right.

313
00:23:25,195 --> 00:23:28,406
- [ Tape: Wind Gusting ]
- [ Tape: Leaves Rustling ]

314
00:23:46,675 --> 00:23:48,926
[ Tape: Man ]
Beautiful night for a walk.

315
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:50,469
[ Tape: Woman ]
Oh, yes, it is.

316
00:23:51,346 --> 00:23:54,849
[ Man ]
Let's take a walk along the river here.

317
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:58,060
- [ Man ] Mmm. Nice.
- [ Woman ] David, look.

318
00:23:58,145 --> 00:24:00,938
- There's someone on the bridge.
- Oh, let's not worry about that.

319
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:03,274
- He's staring right at us.
- Who cares?

320
00:24:03,358 --> 00:24:05,151
- I care!
- Betsy --

321
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:07,736
I don't wanna stay here anymore.
Let's go.

322
00:24:07,821 --> 00:24:09,363
- Yeah, okay.
- What is he doing?

323
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:11,699
- I don't know.
- What is he, a Peeping Tom or something?

324
00:24:11,783 --> 00:24:15,244
Oh, who cares? Come on,
let's walk down here a little further.

325
00:24:15,328 --> 00:24:28,382
[ Clicking ]

326
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:42,521
[ Winding, Clicking ]

