00:25:16,056 --> 00:25:17,431
- [ Loud Bang ]
- [ Air Hissing ]

332
00:25:18,475 --> 00:25:20,226
[ Tires Squealing ]

333
00:25:24,272 --> 00:25:25,439
[ Jack ]
Jesus Christ.

334
00:25:34,449 --> 00:25:52,925
- [ Loud Bang ]
- [ Air Hissing ]

335
00:25:53,927 --> 00:25:55,594
Shit.

336
00:25:59,975 --> 00:26:02,309
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

337
00:26:13,196 --> 00:26:16,198
[ Factory Horn Blowing ]

338
00:26:24,165 --> 00:26:28,168
[ Winding, Clicking ]

339
00:26:35,010 --> 00:26:36,927
[ Winding, Clicking Continues ]

340
00:26:38,972 --> 00:26:40,681
[ Winding, Clicking Stop ]

341
00:28:03,765 --> 00:28:06,558
[ Sally ]
So, uh, you want some coffee?

342
00:28:08,436 --> 00:28:10,562
Huh? You want some coffee?

343
00:28:10,647 --> 00:28:12,523
Mmm. Good morning.

344
00:28:12,607 --> 00:28:14,858
- Hi. How you doin'?
- I'm fine. How are you?

345
00:28:14,943 --> 00:28:17,861
Pretty good.
There you go.

346
00:28:17,946 --> 00:28:20,864
What are you doin' here?
You -- You listenin' to some music?

347
00:28:20,949 --> 00:28:22,741
Mmm. No.

348
00:28:24,327 --> 00:28:26,578
This is my, uh -- this is my job.

349
00:28:26,663 --> 00:28:29,790
- I do sound effects for movies.
- Oh, movies, huh?

350
00:28:29,874 --> 00:28:33,085
Matter of fact, last night I was --
I was out recording some sounds.

351
00:28:33,169 --> 00:28:34,795
What do you mean, sound effects?

352
00:28:34,879 --> 00:28:39,466
Well, you know, when you see a movie
and you hear a door slam...

353
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:41,844
or a bird chirp, or wind, or whatever --

354
00:28:41,928 --> 00:28:46,348
I record those actual sounds
and then I put them in a movie...

355
00:28:46,433 --> 00:28:48,016
and then you see the movie.

356
00:28:48,101 --> 00:28:49,435
- Wow.
- Last night, I --

357
00:28:49,519 --> 00:28:51,812
- Big movies?
- No. Just, uh --

358
00:28:51,896 --> 00:28:54,398
- Just bad ones, unfortunately.
- Oh.

359
00:28:54,482 --> 00:28:56,608
I really love movies, you know.

360
00:28:56,693 --> 00:29:01,113
It's -- It's a very interesting subject to me
because, uh -- because I do makeup.

361
00:29:01,197 --> 00:29:02,614
- Do you?
- Yeah.

362
00:29:02,699 --> 00:29:04,867
I mean, right now it's only
behind the counter at Korvette's...

363
00:29:04,951 --> 00:29:07,202
but I have this dream
about doing makeup for movies.

364
00:29:07,287 --> 00:29:11,540
I mean, like, I've seen these big movie stars --
like Barbra Streisand, you know?

365
00:29:12,292 --> 00:29:14,042
- They don't do it right.
- No?

366
00:29:14,794 --> 00:29:16,545
- I know how to fix a face.
- Really?

367
00:29:16,629 --> 00:29:18,172
- Yeah.
- That's good.

368
00:29:18,923 --> 00:29:20,841
I want you to hear something.
Look.

369
00:29:20,925 --> 00:29:24,803
- [ Click, Tape Reels Rewinding ]
- Last night I was recording some sounds...

370
00:29:24,888 --> 00:29:26,722
and I recorded your accident.

371
00:29:26,806 --> 00:29:28,432
I got the whole thing on tape.

372
00:29:28,516 --> 00:29:31,185
- [ Click, Tape Reels Stop ]
- Oh. You recorded the accident.

373
00:29:31,269 --> 00:29:33,979
Yes, I did, except I don't think
you had an accident.

374
00:29:34,063 --> 00:29:35,981
I think your tire was shot out.

375
00:29:36,065 --> 00:29:38,984
- Oh, that's crazy.
- No, it's not. Listen to this.

376
00:29:39,068 --> 00:29:42,196
All right, now you're gonna hear two sounds.
The first is a gunshot.

377
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,490
And the second is the blowout.

378
00:29:44,574 --> 00:29:46,033
All right? Listen up.

379
00:29:48,495 --> 00:29:51,622
[ Vehicle Approaching ]

380
00:29:51,706 --> 00:29:54,041
- [ Loud Bang ]
- [ Air Hissing ]

381
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:56,043
- [ Tires Squealing ]
- Listen again.

382
00:29:56,127 --> 00:29:58,837
I mean, I heard a noise.
I don't know, maybe that was a gunshot.

383
00:29:58,922 --> 00:30:02,674
But I'll tell you the truth -- I don't really
feature listening to a replay of last night.

384
00:30:02,759 --> 00:30:04,551
It's -- It's kinda depressing.

385
00:30:04,636 --> 00:30:07,137
- [ Tape Deck Clicks Off ]
- Can I ask you something?

386
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:09,932
- What?
- What were you doing with him? With McRyan?

387
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:15,395
That's a very personal question.
That's none of your business.

388
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,981
No -- [ Chuckles ]
I don't mean the details.

389
00:30:18,107 --> 00:30:20,984
- I just wondered why --
- I think I'm getting a cold here and I don't have my makeup or anything.

390
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:24,238
- Hey, come on, Sally, forget it.
- The personal questions. I mean, I don't even know who you are, you know.

391
00:30:24,322 --> 00:30:27,241
Well, I'd like you to get to know who I am.
Hey, how about that drink?

392
00:30:27,325 --> 00:30:29,076
Some other time, okay?

393
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:33,789
Sally, I'm -- Hey, look, I saved your life.
The least you could do is have a drink with me.

394
00:30:35,667 --> 00:30:37,084
- Come on.
- All right.

395
00:30:37,168 --> 00:30:40,212
You can call me at my girlfriend
Judy Demming's. I'll be there.

396
00:30:40,296 --> 00:30:43,298
- She's in the book.
- All right. You telling me the truth?

397
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:46,593
- Yeah.
- All right. I'm gonna call ya.

398
00:30:46,678 --> 00:30:48,136
- Okay.
- Okay.

399
00:30:48,221 --> 00:30:51,223
[ Sirens wailing ]

400
00:30:59,732 --> 00:31:01,733
[ Buzzer Sounding ]

401
00:31:15,331 --> 00:31:17,249
[ Film Soundtrack: Heart Beating ]

402
00:31:17,333 --> 00:31:20,544
Hey, Jack, they got movies of McRyan
getting killed. I just heard it on the radio.

403
00:31:20,628 --> 00:31:22,546
- Maybe they got it on the midday news.
- They got what?

404
00:31:22,630 --> 00:31:24,631
Movies of McRyan getting killed!

405
00:31:25,133 --> 00:31:28,343
Incredible as it may seem,
a local photographer, Manny Karp...

406
00:31:28,428 --> 00:31:31,263
was on the scene of the accident
last night with his camera.

407
00:31:31,347 --> 00:31:32,973
Eye on the City News has learned...

408
00:31:33,057 --> 00:31:36,560
that Mr. Karp sold his film to News Today
magazine late this morning...

409
00:31:36,644 --> 00:31:38,145
- News Today --
- Shh!

410
00:31:38,229 --> 00:31:39,646
for an undisclosed sum of money.

411
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:42,858
Our own Frank Donahue spoke with Mr. Karp
just a few moments ago...

412
00:31:42,942 --> 00:31:45,819
outside the magazine's offices.

413
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:50,324
Well, I'll tell ya. I had gone out there
to try out this new film stock, right?

414
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:53,118
It's a very high speed.
It's good for night shooting.

415
00:31:53,202 --> 00:31:55,495
I, uh -- I do a lot of work at night.

416
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:58,081
So, uh -- so anyway, I'm standing out there,
and all of a sudden...

417
00:31:58,166 --> 00:32:01,209
I-I hear this car
barrelin' down the road, you know.

418
00:32:01,294 --> 00:32:04,713
I didn't pay too much attention
till all of a sudden I hear it startin' to skid.

419
00:32:04,797 --> 00:32:06,715
Well, I, uh -- I wasn't even thinkin'.

420
00:32:06,799 --> 00:32:10,510
I just turned around, my camera's still runnin'
and, bam, I catch him goin' through the railing.

421
00:32:10,595 --> 00:32:12,262
- Mr. Karp! Mr. Karp!
- [ Reporters Clamoring ]

422
00:32:12,347 --> 00:32:14,765
- Frank Donahue, Eye on the City News.
- Yeah, yeah.

423
00:32:14,849 --> 00:32:16,934
Was the governor driving the car?
Was he in control?

424
00:32:17,018 --> 00:32:20,187
Control? [ Chuckles ] It went into the drink,
didn't it? He wasn't in no control.

425
00:32:20,271 --> 00:32:23,023
- Was he alone? Was he alone in the car?
- Well, I didn't see anybody.

426
00:32:23,107 --> 00:32:25,525
[ Female Reporter ]
Why didn't you go to the police that night?

427
00:32:25,610 --> 00:32:29,363
- Oh, no. No, no, no, no.
- [ Karp ] Lady, no cop ever did anything for me.

428
00:32:29,489 --> 00:32:32,532
- Hey, Jack.
- They ain't gonna give me the kind of money these guys here are givin' me.

429
00:32:32,617 --> 00:32:34,451
- Wh-where are you goin'?
- I gotta go.

430
00:32:34,535 --> 00:32:37,663
- You gotta go? What about the auditions?
- [ TV: Karp Continues ]

431
00:32:37,747 --> 00:32:40,540
[ News Dealer ]
Exclusive photos. McRyan's death.

432
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:44,378
One at a time, please.
Exclusive photos. McRyan's death.

433
00:32:46,965 --> 00:32:48,840
- It's about time you showed up.
- Is Rick here?

434
00:32:48,967 --> 00:32:52,427
- No, but Sam's here and he's got those girls he wants you to hear.
- Let me have the key. Come on, come on.

435
00:32:53,721 --> 00:32:55,847
- What about Sam and the girls?
- I'll do it later.

436
00:32:55,932 --> 00:32:59,935
- [ Projectors whirring ]
- [ Tape Audio: Sound Effects, Musical Cues ]

437
00:33:02,438 --> 00:33:05,691
[ Chattering, Faint ]

438
00:33:12,573 --> 00:33:14,616
- [ Knocking ]
- [ Sam ] Jack?

439
00:33:14,701 --> 00:33:16,326
Yo, Jack!

440
00:33:17,328 --> 00:33:19,871
Come on, open up! It's Sam.

441
00:33:20,915 --> 00:33:22,374
Jack?

442
00:33:23,626 --> 00:33:26,420
[ Footsteps Receding ]

443
00:34:42,121 --> 00:35:16,029
[ Shutter Clicks ]

444
00:35:32,046 --> 00:35:35,298
This is the pivotal moment in the film.
You gotta realize that.

445
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:37,300
Hey, Jack!
Where the fuck are you going?

446
00:35:37,385 --> 00:35:41,138
- Sam, I'll be right back.
- I need you now! Now get in here!

447
00:35:42,306 --> 00:35:43,473
Aah!

448
00:35:43,558 --> 00:35:45,433
- Aah!
- Aah!

449
00:35:45,518 --> 00:35:47,477
- What do you think?
- Keep lookin'.

450
00:35:47,562 --> 00:35:49,771
Keep lookin'?
Hey, Jack, what are you talking about?

451
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:07,747
- Sorry, Jack. I'm all stacked up.
